From: Christian Walter <christian.walter@9elements.com>
Date: Sun, 16 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ikvm: add XRGB32 framebuffer support

Add support for V4L2_PIX_FMT_XRGB32 pixel format. Video capture
devices that output raw 32-bit XRGB pixels (such as the HPE GXP
thumbnail video engine) are not handled by upstream obmc-ikvm,
which only supports JPEG and RGB24. Without this, the XRGB32
format falls through to the default case and no frames are sent.

Handle XRGB32 the same way as RGB24: copy the frame data into the
VNC framebuffer vector and mark the full screen as modified.

Upstream-Status: Pending
Signed-off-by: Christian Walter <christian.walter@9elements.com>
---
 ikvm_server.cpp | 5 +++++
 ikvm_video.cpp  | 3 ++-
 2 files changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/ikvm_server.cpp b/ikvm_server.cpp
index 9274a9b..a1b2c3d 100644
--- a/ikvm_server.cpp
+++ b/ikvm_server.cpp
@@ -159,6 +159,11 @@ void Server::sendFrame()

         switch (video.getPixelformat())
         {
+            case V4L2_PIX_FMT_XRGB32:
+                framebuffer.assign(data, data + video.getFrameSize());
+                rfbMarkRectAsModified(server, 0, 0, video.getWidth(),
+                                      video.getHeight());
+                break;
             case V4L2_PIX_FMT_RGB24:
                 framebuffer.assign(data, data + video.getFrameSize());
                 rfbMarkRectAsModified(server, 0, 0, video.getWidth(),
diff --git a/ikvm_video.cpp b/ikvm_video.cpp
index 3445715..2f637d6 100644
--- a/ikvm_video.cpp
+++ b/ikvm_video.cpp
@@ -459,7 +459,8 @@ void Video::start()
     width = fmt.fmt.pix.width;
     pixelformat = fmt.fmt.pix.pixelformat;

-    if (pixelformat != V4L2_PIX_FMT_RGB24 && pixelformat != V4L2_PIX_FMT_JPEG)
+    if (pixelformat != V4L2_PIX_FMT_RGB24 && pixelformat != V4L2_PIX_FMT_JPEG
+        && pixelformat != V4L2_PIX_FMT_XRGB32)
     {
         log<level::ERR>("Pixel Format not supported",
                         entry("PIXELFORMAT=%d", pixelformat));
